<div class="min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0a]">
  <article class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 sm:px-12 pt-12 pb-8">
    <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[#a0a0a0] hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8" do %>
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
        <path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/><path d="M19 12H5"/>
      </svg>
      Back to Home
    <% end %>

    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[#606060] text-sm">Last updated: January 2025</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Overview</h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">
          YTgify is a browser extension designed to create GIFs from YouTube
          videos while maintaining strict privacy protections. We believe in
          complete transparency about how your data is handled.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Zero-Collection Model
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          YTgify does <strong class="text-white">NOT</strong>:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-[#a0a0a0] space-y-2">
          <li>Collect personal information</li>
          <li>Track user behavior or analytics</li>
          <li>Send any data to external servers</li>
          <li>Share data with third parties</li>
          <li>Use cookies for tracking purposes</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Local Processing
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">
          All GIF creation and processing happens entirely on your device.
          The extension stores GIFs and user settings exclusively on your
          device using your browser's built-in storage systems. No
          information is transmitted to external servers or third parties.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Data You Control
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You maintain complete authority over your data. You can remove all
          stored information at any time by:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-[#a0a0a0] space-y-2">
          <li>Uninstalling the extension</li>
          <li>Clearing extension data through browser settings</li>
          <li>Using the built-in deletion features</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          <strong class="text-white">Your GIFs are yours alone.</strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Required Permissions
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The extension requires specific permissions to function:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-[#a0a0a0] space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Active tab access:</strong> To
            interact with YouTube video pages
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Download capability:</strong> To
            save GIFs to your device
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong class="text-white">Storage:</strong> To save your
            preferences locally
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          These permissions serve only the core GIF-creation function and
          are never used for data collection.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          YouTube Terms of Service
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">
          YTgify respects YouTube's Terms of Service and does not
          circumvent any platform restrictions. The extension only works
          with publicly available video content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Open Source Transparency
        </h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">
          YTgify's code is publicly available on
          <a
            href="https://github.com/neonwatty/ytgify"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-ytg-pink hover:underline"
          >
            GitHub
          </a>,
          allowing independent verification of our privacy claims. We
          encourage security researchers and users to review our code.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-[#a0a0a0] leading-relaxed">
          For privacy-related questions or concerns, you can reach us via:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-[#a0a0a0] space-y-2 mt-4">
          <li>
            GitHub Issues:
            <a
              href="https://github.com/neonwatty/ytgify/issues"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="text-ytg-pink hover:underline"
            >
              github.com/neonwatty/ytgify/issues
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            Email:
            <a
              href="mailto:neonwatty@gmail.com"
              class="text-ytg-pink hover:underline"
            >
              neonwatty@gmail.com
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
  <%= render "marketing/shared/footer" %>
</div>
